<br>
***<br>
<br>
It seems that the geniuses at Verant decided to give Dark Elves the advantage when it comes to necromancy, since every non-expansion spell is available at the Neriak vendors.  So, whenever Musty hits a new spell circle, I create a Teir'Dal mule on Caed's account and sit him just outside of the Neriak entrance while I bring Musty to Nektulos.<br>
<br>
During this time, I put the [AFK] tag on the mule, because I'm usually not even watching that monitor, and don't want to offend anyone who tries to chat to a nonresponsive avatar.  This almost always works, but one day, a not-so-bright young one decided to approach my mule.<br>
<br>
&quot;whats your guild mean?&quot;<br>
<br>
I didn't respond, since I figured he was probably talking to someone right inside the entryway.  However, he persisted.<br>
<br>
&quot;what does your guild stand for?&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm chuckling to myself, thinking that he can't possibly believe that AFK is a guild name.<br>
<br>
&quot;can i join your guild?&quot;<br>
<br>
I still don't answer, as I'm mainly concentrating on getting Musty to Nektulos, but I can't help but wait for what the newbie is going to say next.<br>
<br>
&quot;screw u ill remember your rudeness&quot;<br>
<br>
Then, a minute later, in /shout...<br>
<br>
&quot;what does the guild AFK stand for?&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm pretty certain he was laughed out of the zone.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
***<br>
<br>
This encounter happened more recently--only about a week ago, if I remember correctly.  Musty was plopped in the EC tunnel entrance, /auctioning for the leve 39 drop-only spells, and buying bone chips from newbies, some who didn't even ask whether she was interested; they just stuck a stack of bone chips in my trade window.  I wasn't complaining, though.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It just meant less auctioning for me.  But then the fun begins.<br>
<br>
A bard runs right up in front of me, and invites me into his group.  I do a /who on him, and see that he's only level 5.  I was a little low on hit points from using my Call of Bones spell, so I accepted his invitation, thinking he was going to use his healing song to try to earn a few gold.  Of course, I grow a bit suspicious after he doesn't do anything helpful, and the other person (a level 13 warrior) in the group says &quot;yay!&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Musty:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Um, why did you invite me?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  your going to help us<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Musty:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Help you do what?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  we died and lost our corps your going to help us find them<br>
<br>
I was about to disband right then and there, because I had already summoned a pretty damned good pet, and planned on slaying any stray griffins that roamed about, but I figured, Eh, why not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Musty:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Where did you die?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  in a lake<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Warrior:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  our corpses are in the lake and the pirannas keep killing us<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Musty:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Why did you go in the lake in the first place?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  i dont know<br>
<br>
I'm a little frustrated right now, seeing as how these two don't seem like the sharpest nails in the bunch.  But, I /follow the bard.  When he starts leading me all the way up the side of the south zone wall, I just go to WC on my <br>
own and figure he and the warrior will make it there on their own.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  bear!!  kill it!!!<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Musty:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Sorry, I can't.  I'm already in WC.<br>
<br>
The bard died, and the warrior zoned into WC shortly thereafter.  I go to the lake, and tell the warrior that I'm going to drag his corpse out and pull it to the zone line.  He agrees.  Of course, I didn't know he had multiple corpses in the lake.  He eventually came to the lake, and after a few pulls of naked corpses, we found the corpse with all the goodies on it.<br>
<br>
Then, the bard finally makes his way back.  However, he dives right into the water and promptly gets eaten by the pirahnas.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  why didnt u save me????<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Musty:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  You had about five piranhas on you, and my lifetap can't kill them in one shot.  I would've wasted my mana trying.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  thats why we brought u with us to kill all the pirannas so i could get my corps u dummy!!!!<br>
<br>
Yes, I was pissed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Musty:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Look, first of all, I wasn't <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>asked</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> if I was willing to come help you.  And just for reference, no, I wasn't willing, but I did so anyway, but it seemed like you genuinely needed help.  Secondly, it's your fault you died that time, because you didn't even alert me as to when you were diving into the water.<br>
<br>
That shut the bard up for a little bit, most likely because half of the words in that little lecture he couldn't even understand.  I guess he was making his way through EC, when all of a sudden...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  bear!!  help me!!!<br>
<br>
I guess he died again, 'cause he threw a fit, telling me how much I sucked, and logged.  At least the warrior thanked me heartily for finding his corpse.  I don't understand how the bard could've died to the bear, though, seeing as how he could've easily outrun it with Selo's.  &lt;shrugs&gt;  His fault.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
