<br>
<br>
So I decide to start pulling thinking maybe if I pull blues the monk wont get shredded so fast, but again, the cleric is practically having a heart attack trying to keep up with things.  I finally comment about it and ask what her armor class is (and this is with the clerics Symbol and Skin Like Steel and that cleric Armor spell), 510 she says.  I couldnt believe it, lvl 31 buffed to the hilt and her AC is lower then my piddley Druid AC?  &quot;How much weight do you have on you?&quot; I ask.  &quot;Uhhh, 35 stones, why?&quot; she says.  I couldnt believe it, she didnt seem to realize the huge effect carrying over that certain weight (can't remember, 13 or 15?) has on a Monk's AC.  I run up and inspect her and she's not too bad off, had a few absurdly heavy items for a monk like Iksar Scaled Gloves that weigh like 4 so I ask her what she's carrying? &quot;Just 4 backpacks&quot; she says.  Now since they weigh 3 each, that right there is almost enough to put her over the limit.  <br>
<br>
Anyways, I thought every monk had learned by lvl 3 or so about the whole weight thing and knew to carry Large Sewing kits or some other lightweight container, I just couldnt believe she had made it all the way to 31 playing that way and I hate to think of all the clerics she's given Ulcers to over that time. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.geocities.com/damienespo/Brambler-1.jpg"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ubrambler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brambler</A> at: 1/5/01 2:28:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ilrissa>Ilrissa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 11:51:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stupid newbie encounters.</span><hr size=1> Another stupid newbie ancounter. This time Queshu is sitting outside of NQ gate and up wanders this 3rd lvl warrior. <br>
<br>
Warrior: What lvl are you?<br>
Queshu: I am 14<br>
Warrior: Do you have any PP<br>
<br>
I had just leveled so I had cleaned out the bank for new spells<br>
<br>
Queshu: got about a hundred plat on me<br>
Warrior: Can you spare some money I am new<br>
<br>
I am looking at this guy he has got better armor than I have<br>
and he is only lvl 3.<br>
<br>
Well time to toy with him.<br>
<br>
Queshu: Sure but I need you to get a spell for me.<br>
Warrior: What spell?<br>
Queshu: Sicken (low lvl shaman spell wich i already have)<br>
Warrior: Where is it at?<br>
Queshu: In Everfrost<br>
<br>
about this time a wizzie is busting up laughing in tells thought it was hilarious.<br>
<br>
Warrior: Where is it at.<br>
<br>
I proceed to give him directions.<br>
<br>
Warrior: I'll get killed in Blackburrow.<br>
<br>
Obviously he isnt that new. By this time the wizzie is almost peeing herself. When i finished medding he was gone.<br>
<br>
Try this tactic. The worse thing that could happen is you give the newbie a couple of gold and doesnt come back with your spell. Most of the time they will give up.  <br>
